1635-4|language=French}}\n* {{cite book|last=Ostrower|first=Gary|year=1995|title=The League of Nations from 1919 to 1929 (Partners for Peace|publisher=[[Avery Publishing|Avery Publishing Group]]|isbn=978-0895296368|url=https://archive.org/details/leagueofnationsf00ostr}}\n* {{cite journal | last = Shine| first = Cormac| title = Papal Diplomacy by Proxy? Catholic Internationalism at the League of Nations' International Committee on Intellectual Cooperation | journal = [[The Journal of Ecclesiastical History]] | volume = 69| issue = 4| pages = 785\u2013805| date = 2018 | doi = 10.1017/S0022046917002731}}\n* Swart, William J. \"The League of Nations and the Irish Question.\" ''Sociological Quarterly'' 36.3 (1995): 465\u2013481.\n* {{cite book |last= Walters| first = F. P. |year= 1952 |title = A History of the League of Nations |publisher= Oxford University Press |url= https://libraryresources.unog.ch/ld.php?content_id=32146299| ref=walters}}\n* Yearwood, Peter J. ''Guarantee of Peace: The League of Nations in British Policy 1914\u20131925'' (Oxford UP, 2009).\n{{refend}}\n\n==== Specialised topics ====\n{{refbegin|30em}}\n* {{cite book |last = Archer |first = Clive |title = International Organizations |publisher = Routledge |year = 2001 |isbn = 978-0-415-24690-3 |ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book |last = Baer |first = George W |title = Test Case: Italy, Ethiopia, and the League of Nations|publisher = Hoover Institution Press |year = 1976 |isbn = 978-0-8179-6591-4 |ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book |last = Barnett |first = Correlli |title = The Collapse of British Power |publisher = Eyre Methuen |year = 1972 |isbn = 978-0-413-27580-6 |ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book |last = Baumslag |first = Naomi |year = 2005 |title = Murderous Medicine: Nazi Doctors, Human Experimentation, and Typhus |publisher = Praeger |isbn = 978-0-275-98312-3 |ref = harv |url-access = registration |url = https://archive.org/details/murderousmedicin0000baum }}\n* {{cite book |last = Bell |first = P.M.H |year = 2007 |title = The Origins of the Second World War in Europe |publisher = Pearson Education Limited |isbn = 978-1-4058-4028-6 |ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book |last = Bethell |first = Leslie |year = 1991 |title = The Cambridge History of Latin America: Volume VIII 1930 to the Present |publisher = Cambridge University Press |isbn = 978-0-521-26652-9 |ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book |last1 = Bouchet-Saulnier |first1 = Fran\u00e7oise |last2 = Brav |first2 = Laura |last3 = Olivier |first3 = Clementine |year = 2007 |title = The Practical Guide to Humanitarian Law |url = https://archive.org/details/practicalguideto0000bouc |url-access = registration |publisher = Rowman & Littlefield |isbn = 978-0-7425-5496-2 |ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book |last = Churchill |first = Winston |year = 1986 |title = The Second World War: Volume I The Gathering Storm |publisher = Houghton Mifflin Books |isbn = 978-0-395-41055-4 |ref = harv |url-access = registration |url = https://archive.org/details/gatheringstorm00chur_0 }}\n* {{cite book |last = Crampton |first = Ben |year = 1996 |title = Atlas of Eastern Europe in the Twentieth Century |publisher = Routledge |isbn = 978-0-415-16461-0 |ref = harv}}\n*{{cite book|ref=harv|last1=Everard|first1=Myriam|last2=de Haan|first2=Francisca |title=Rosa Manus (1881-1942): The International Life and Legacy of a Jewish Dutch Feminist|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=MydoDQAAQBAJ&pg=PA68|year=2016|publisher=BRILL|location=Leiden, The Netherlands|isbn=978-90-04-33318-5}}\n* {{cite book |last1 = Frowein |first1 = Jochen A |last2 = R\u00fcdiger |first2 = Wolfrum |year = 2000 |title = Max Planck Yearbook of United Nations Law |publisher = Martinus Nijhoff Publishers |isbn = 978-90-411-1403-7 |ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book |last = Goldblat |first = Jozef |year = 2002 |title = Arms control: the new guide to negotiations and agreements |publisher = SAGE Publications Ltd |isbn = 978-0-7619-4016-6 |ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book |last = Gorodetsky |first = Gabriel |year = 1994 |t