e=Report for Selected Countries and Subjects|website=www.imf.org|language=en-US|access-date=10 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.imf.org/external/pubs/ft/weo/2019/01/weodata/weorept.aspx?pr.x=75&pr.y=6&sy=1980&ey=2024&scsm=1&ssd=1&sort=country&ds=.&br=1&c=158&s=NGDP_RPCH,PPPGDP,PPPPC,PCPIPCH,LUR,GGXWDG_NGDP&grp=0&a=|title=Report for Selected Countries and Subjects|website=www.imf.org|access-date=12 April 2019}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n!Year\n!GDP<br /><small>(in bil. US$ PPP)</small>\n!GDP per capita<br /><small href=\"Paris\">(in US$ PPP)</small>\n!GDP growth<br /><small>(real)</small>\n!Inflation rate<br /><small>(in Percent)</small>\n!Unemployment <br /><small>(in Percent)</small>\n!Government debt<br /><small>(in % of GDP)</small>\n|-\n|1980\n|1,041.7\n|8,921\n|{{Increase}}3.2 %\n|{{increaseNegative}}7.8 %\n|2.0 %\n|48.8 %\n|-\n|1981\n|{{Increase}}1,187,0\n|{{Increase}}10,091\n|{{Increase}}4.2 %\n|{{increaseNegative}}4.9 %\n|{{increaseNegative}}2.2 %\n|{{increaseNegative}}54.0 %\n|-\n|1982\n|{{Increase}}1,302.4\n|{{Increase}}10,995\n|{{Increase}}3.3 %\n|{{increaseNegative}}2.7 %\n|{{increaseNegative}}2.4 %\n|{{increaseNegative}}59.0 %\n|-\n|1983\n|{{Increase}}1,401.5\n|{{Increase}}11,750\n|{{Increase}}3.5 %\n|{{increase}}1.9 %\n|{{increaseNegative}}2.7 %\n|{{increaseNegative}}64.9 %\n|-\n|1984\n|{{Increase}}1,516.5\n|{{Increase}}12,632\n|{{Increase}}4.5 %\n|{{increaseNegative}}2.3 %\n|{{Steady}}2.7 %\n|{{increaseNegative}}67.0 %\n|-\n|1985\n|{{Increase}}1,647.0\n|{{Increase}}13,634\n|{{Increase}}5.2 %\n|{{increase}}2.0 %\n|{{decreasePositive}}2.6 %\n|{{increaseNegative}}69.7 %\n|-\n|1986\n|{{Increase}}1,736.1\n|{{Increase}}14,295\n|{{Increase}}3.3 %\n|{{increase}}0.6 %\n|{{increaseNegative}}2.8 %\n|{{increaseNegative}}75.5 %\n|-\n|1987\n|{{Increase}}1,864.6\n|{{Increase}}15,279\n|{{Increase}}4.7 %\n|{{Increase}}0.1 %\n|{{increaseNegative}}2.9 %\n|{{increaseNegative}}77.3 %\n|-\n|1988\n|{{Increase}}2,060.8\n